title: Top travel photos of the week
persons: MICHAEL DALDER/REUTERS LUCY NICHOLSON/REUTERS MIKE BLAKE/REUTERS Agung
text:
Top travel photos of the week Last updated 11:09, September 18 2015 Ulet Ifansasti/REUTERS Ulet Ifansasti/Reuters Ben Pruchnie/GETTYIMAGES MARIANA BAZO/REUTERS JIM YOUNG/REUTERS MICHAEL DALDER/REUTERS LUCY NICHOLSON/REUTERS MIKE BLAKE/REUTERS Agung Parameswara/GETTYIMAGES Agung Parameswara/GETTYIMAGES JAIME SALDARRIAGA/REUTERS CHINA DAILY/REUTERS Paul Childs/REUTERS EDGAR SU/REUTERS ANINDITO MUKHERJEE/REUTERS SERGEI KARPUKHIN/REUTERS RICK WILKING/REUTERS PHIL NOBLE/REUTERS ChinaFotoPress/GETTYIMAGES 
Child jockeys compete in the traditional horse races as part of Moyo festival in Sumbawa Island, West Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia. Horse races known as Maen Jaran are part of culture for the people of Sumbawa where the horse has an important role in all aspects of their daily life, including transportation and culture. The horseback-racing tradition involves child jockeys aged 5-10 years riding bareback. For each race, the jockeys get paid around Rp.50.000 or US$5. 
Child jockeys wait at the starting box as they prepare for the race during the traditional horse races as part of Moyo festival. 
The Shaolin Monks have travelled from their temple in the foothills of the Song Shang mountains in China's Henan province to perform the ultimate display of Kung Fu, weapons and combat displays and choreography in a new show at London's Peacock Theatre. 
A volunteer of Animal Science and Well-being Organization (ORCA), observes a sea lion, named Fabiana, on the deck of a boat in front of Palomino island, in Callao, Peru. Four young sea lions returned to the wild after being rescued by marine biologists. 
A boy walks among some of the 3,000 flags placed in memory of the lives lost in the September 11, 2001 attacks, at a park in Winnetka, Illinois. 
Andreas Steinfatt of the Paulaner brewery unveils a huge beer mug figure in preparation for the Oktoberfest in Munich, Germany. Millions of beer drinkers from around the world are expected to attend the 182nd Oktoberfest beer festival, which opens on September 19. 
Jenny Castro, 36, holds her 11-month-old daughter Gabriella Castro up at the Nashuva Spiritual Community Jewish New Year celebration on Venice Beach in Los Angeles, California. As Jews take part in the Tashlich prayer, a Rosh Hashanah ritual, bread crumbs are tossed into the waters to symbolically cast away sins. 
California State lifeguard Jamie O'Donnell looks out over the low tide before he closes down his lifeguard tower on the beach in Cardiff, California. 
Foreign tourists carry a giant sea turtle as they help Indonesian Marine Police to release sea turtles at Kuta Beach. 
A sea turtle walks to the sea after being released by Indonesian Marine Police at Kuta Beach. 
A woman participates in the Cali Tattoo Festival in Cali, Colombia. 
Visitors look at a "moon" balloon on display ahead of the Mid-Autumn Festival at a square in Nanjing, Jiangsu province, China. The Mid-Autumn Festival is celebrated on the 15th day of the eighth month in the lunar calendar during a full moon. 
Samoa's squad pose for a team photograph in Brighton during their welcome ceremony for the RWC 2015 
Tourists look at the Singapore Flyer observatory wheel shrouded by haze in Singapore. Indonesia said on Friday it will send more than 1,000 troops to fight fires in southern Sumatra, as smoke makes thousands sick, delays flights and pushes air quality to unhealthy levels in neighboring Singapore and Malaysia. 
Devotees prepare to load an idol of the Hindu god Ganesh, the deity of prosperity, onto a truck to a place of worship on the first day of the ten-day-long Ganesh Chaturthi festival in New Delhi, India. 
People have a meal while sitting at table with food models as the gastronomic festival "Moscow autumn" takes place near the Kremlin (R) and the State Historical Museum (L) in central Moscow, Russia. 
A power boat cruises with Phoebe the dog on the bow, through a cut below Castle Rock in Lake Powell near Page, Arizona. Lake Powell on the Colorado River provides water for Nevada, Arizona and California. A severe drought in recent years, combined with withdrawals that many believe are not sustainable, has reduced its levels to only about 42 percent of its capacity. 
The Port of Liverpool building is seen reflected in the windows of a modern office block in Liverpool northern Britain. The Port of Liverpool building was built in 1907 and is the former home of the Mersey Docks and Harbour Board. 
Fishing boats set off from Shipu port for fishing in Ningbo, China. Thousands of fishing boats set sail for fishing after three and a half months. 1 of 19 
Here is our round up of the top travel photos from around the world. 
Do you have a favourite? Let us know in the comments Ad Feedback Ulet Ifansasti/Reuters
